JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 132
EP  - 143
VL  - 23
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This research supports the conclusion that the effects of handicap-based social-psychological factors can be moderated by a supportive vocational environment to the extent that most perceptibly physically handicapped will perform over a career as well as the nonhandicapped. Eight different measures of performance were analyzed.
AB  - This research supports the conclusion that the effects of handicap-based social-psychological factors can be moderated by a supportive vocational environment to the extent that most perceptibly physically handicapped will perform over a career as well as the nonhandicapped. Eight different measures of performance were analyzed.
