TY  - JOUR
T1  - Privacy at Work: Architectural Correlates of Job Satisfaction and Job Performance
AU  - Sundstrom, Eric
AU  - Burt, Robert E.
AU  - Kamp, Douglas
Y1  - 1980/03/01
PY  - 1980
DA  - 1980/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255498
DO  - 10.5465/255498
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 101
EP  - 117
VL  - 23
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Three correlational studies examined relationships among architectural privacy, psychological privacy, job satisfaction, and job performance. Results of all three studies showed architectural privacy associated with psychological privacy. Both forms of privacy were associated with satisfaction with workspace and job satisfaction. Architectural privacy showed a limited, positive relationship with job performance in clerical and mechanical employees.
AB  - Three correlational studies examined relationships among architectural privacy, psychological privacy, job satisfaction, and job performance. Results of all three studies showed architectural privacy associated with psychological privacy. Both forms of privacy were associated with satisfaction with workspace and job satisfaction. Architectural privacy showed a limited, positive relationship with job performance in clerical and mechanical employees.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/255498
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/255498
Y2  - 2026/04/24
