T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 5
EP  - 20
VL  - 23
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In a study of the effects of strategic planning, statistical tests did not indicate significant differences between the returns earned by shareholders of planning firms and nonplanning firms. There was indication of a transitory reduction in the riskiness of planning firms after the initiation of planning, relative to nonplanning firms, where risk is measured in a capital asset pricing model framework.
AB  - In a study of the effects of strategic planning, statistical tests did not indicate significant differences between the returns earned by shareholders of planning firms and nonplanning firms. There was indication of a transitory reduction in the riskiness of planning firms after the initiation of planning, relative to nonplanning firms, where risk is measured in a capital asset pricing model framework.
