AU  - Bain, Trevor
Y1  - 1980/03/01
PY  - 1980
DA  - 1980/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255501
DO  - 10.5465/255501
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 144
EP  - 149
VL  - 23
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses the role of sex differences in occupational aspirations. According to the results of this study, processes of socialization in the United States at the time of publication encourage occupational aspirations leaning toward professional rather than managerial careers. The study asserts that these processes reinforce existing sex role stereotypes in regards to occupational groupings. Factors labeled by the study that affect occupational aspirations include societal cultural values and the impact of a career on family life.
AB  - The article discusses the role of sex differences in occupational aspirations. According to the results of this study, processes of socialization in the United States at the time of publication encourage occupational aspirations leaning toward professional rather than managerial careers. The study asserts that these processes reinforce existing sex role stereotypes in regards to occupational groupings. Factors labeled by the study that affect occupational aspirations include societal cultural values and the impact of a career on family life.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/255501
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/255501
